Nubia has unveiled its Red Magic smartphone, aimed at mobile gamers. The device sports a unique design, complete with RGB lighting zone on its back panel. It is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 835 chipset with 8GB of RAM and boasts a 6-inch 2,160 x 1,080 display. Nubia said the Red Magic is aimed at “extreme gamers”, and includes an advanced cooling system along with a customisable “game button” on the side of the device. It also sports a 24MP primary camera and an 8MP front-facing lens, along with a 3,800mAh battery. Nubia’s’ Red Magic smartphone will be available on Indiegogo from 26 April and will be priced at $399.  